description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an enthusiastic and dedicated Registered Nurse to join our friendly and committed Clinical Haematology team as the Deputy Sister on a 12 month secondment or fixed term. The Centre for Clinical Haematology is a nationally recognised centre of excellence for the treatment of haematological malignancies covering a large geographical area. The department is currently open from 8am to 8pm Monday to Friday and 8-4 on Saturday’s including bank holidays.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This role will include working with the Haematology Day Case and outpatient Sister to lead and support the day case and outpatient team to provide an excellent high quality service for our haematology patients. The successful candidate will be provided with an opportunity to develop clinical skills and knowledge, progress in leadership competency and undertake service improvement initiatives in conjunction with our service progression to accommodate our patients changing health care needs, Trust objectives and national targets.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are an experienced motivated registered nurse with an interest in haematology and ready to develop both clinical and leadership skills in a supportive environment we would love to hear from you.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For the above post it is essential you submit supporting information which reflects your interest and experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name-Angela Warriner&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title-Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
